{{Infobox person | name =Augustine Njoku Obi | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date =1930 | birth_place = [[Owerri]], [[Imo State]], [[Nigeria]] | othername = | nationality = Nigerian | citizenship = Nigerian | occupation ={{flatlist| * educator *microbiologist *researcher}} | parents = | relatives = | yearsactive = |known for =[[Cholera vaccine]] |awards= | website = }}
'''Augustine Njoku Obi''' (1930 – 2003) was a [[Nigerian]] Professor of [[virology]] and former President of the [[Nigerian Academy of Science]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Celebration of the Great Life of Prof. Augustine Nwaneri Uzoma Njoku-Obi, K.s.c: 1930-2003 : Diocese of Owerri, Emmanuel Anglican Church|date=2003}}</ref> He was known for developing a [[cholera vaccine]] approved as [[efficacy]] in 1971 by [[WHO]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newsexpressngr.com/news/detail.php?news=2590|title=Igbo scholar who disgraced Femi Fani-Kayode strikes again •Sets records straight on Bini, Igbo, Yoruba, Efik, Kanuri & Fulani greats|work=News Express Nigeria|accessdate=June 9, 2015}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://sunnewsonline.com/new/ibehs-aids-cure-claim/ |title=Ibeh’s AIDS cure claim |work=The Sun News |accessdate=June 9, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709194155/http://sunnewsonline.com/new/ibehs-aids-cure-claim/ |archivedate=July 9, 2015 |df= }}</ref> In 1985, he was elected President of the [[Nigerian Academy of Science]] to succeeded Professor [[Emmanuel Emovon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nas.org.ng/fellowship/members-of-council/ |title=Members of Council |work=Nigerian Academy of Science |accessdate=June 7, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707061854/http://www.nas.org.ng/fellowship/members-of-council/ |archivedate=July 7, 2015 |df= }}</ref>
